<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E03FF8D489054E0FEAEFC14" box="[160,267,972,996]" captionStart="PLATE 19" captionStartId="76.[151,233,1880,1903]" captionTargetBox="[183,1379,217,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-108@76.[166,1421,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="PLATE 19. A–C. Male genitalia. D–F. Chelae. A. Anteon autumnale, holotype (from Olmi 1991). B. A. autumnale from China. C. A. biprocessum, holotype (from Xu &amp; He, 1997b). D. A. becvari, holotype (from Olmi 2000b). E. A. bengalense, holotype (from Olmi 1984). F. A. blanduscutum, holotype (from Xu et al. 1996). Scale bar 0.20 mm for A, B and C, 0.26 mm for D, 0.30 mm for E, 0.10 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278438" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278438/files/figure.png" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Plate 19F</figureCitation>
